information.faqr1: BambooDefI is a platform based on ETH, BSC and VELAS Blockchain, you can use Metamask, Trust Wallet, VelasWallet or Walletconnect.
information.faqr2: It is a lottery system that takes place every ten days, you can buy tickets with Bamboo and participate. There are ten winners who will share the Bamboo accumulated from the purchase of tickets, one of them is the BambooVault, which will dedicate its share to the support of the system, and the rest will be determined randomly among the competing tickets.
information.faqr3: Bamboo Burn Yearly Party. An annual lottery system, in which Bamboo is burned to buy tickets. The prize is 10% of the Bamboo accumulated in the BambooVault over the year, and there is a single winner determined at random from all participating tickets
information.faqr4: The BambooDeFi team is working hard to offer the card as soon as possible. When it is available it will be communicated through the official channels.
information.faqr5: Bamboo can be implemented in all ATMs sold by AuroraCryptoMachines. We do not yet have an exact date for implementation.
information.faqr6: The community decides everything from developer fees, adding new Pools, rebalancing and even deactivating Pools. Votes are based on the BAMBOO GROW RATIO. This is a voting system, where you get 1 vote per Bamboo in your wallet.
information.faqr7: We are continuously in development, it is publicly visible at: GITHUB. The SourceCode of the main SmartContract can also be viewed at EtherScan.
information.faqr8: We are a software development company based in Spain, visit: www.nexxyolabs.com.
information.faqr9: He is like that, you can see his face and the rest of the team at www.nexxyolabs.com.
information.faqr10: They symbolise peace, perseverance and patience; they are strong yet sweet, as well as being a symbol of good luck and the team's favourite animal.
information.faqr11: We collaborate with the Chengdu Giant Panda Research Foundation, donating 5% of the profits obtained with BambooDeFi.
information.faqr12: It is a process of elimination of the token so that it cannot be used or traded, it will be reflected in the network of: <a href="https://etherscan.io/token/0xf56842Af3B56Fd72d17cB103f92d027bBa912e89" target="_blank">EtherScan<a>.
information.faqr13: All contracts were audited by RED4SEC.
information.faqr14: An audit validates the code by an external company, <a href="https://red4sec.com/" target="_blank">RED4SEC<a> in the case of BambooDeFi, ensuring the solidity, security and eliminating any possible vulnerability of it, meeting all requirements to operate without any danger to users.

walletmenu.resume: In this section you can check the status of your wallet (Total Bamboo, Bamboo in stake and temporality).  Also from this section you will be able to perform QuickSwaps, to create instant liquidity pools without having to search in the list of pairs.

liquidity.resume: In this section you can see the active pools and the history. In the active pools you can see the value in USDT blocked in each pool, its yield per 1000 USDT, the daily, monthly and annual ROI, its available amount, amount in stake and the rewards.

raindrop.resume: In this section you will be able to participate in the raffle that will take place every ten days.
raindrop.buyExplain: Exchange Bamboo for tickets to the next lottery
raindrop.errorCoin: Not enough Bamboo in your wallet

pairs.resume: List of pairs permanently updated, where it will be shown its Symbol, liquidity, volume (24h/7days), Fees (24h) , 1year fees/liquidity (based on the volume of 24 hours).

governance.resume: In this section you could view current and past proposals, clicking on the link you will be send to the snapshot page, were you can vote and launch new proposals if you have a wallet with bamboo inside. Proposals must have a period of at least 48 hours to be considered valid. Notice that oficial language for the proposals is English.

vault.resume: In this section the BAMBOOVAULT accounts will be shown in detail (SOLIDARITY WALLET, TEAM WALLET), as well as a list with the token burns made and the programmed ones. In addition, you will be able to see the remaining blocking time of each Bamboo contained in the team wallet.

field.disclaimer:
Set at least 2001 Bamboo and select a Pool with stake, 2000 Bamboo will be blocked for 7 days, and in adition you receive at least one Bamboo Seed (Seed).

You can add more Seeds if you want.

You could withdraw this Bamboo and Seeds in seven days, and when you withdraw you will be rewarded with the 2000 Bamboo staked previously and the equivalent Seeds in Bamboo value at the moment.

Aditionaly you receive the 0,04% proportional to the Seeds staked in the selected Pool if you have BLp staked at least for 60 days.'

guide.title4: How to Add Liquidity to a Pool
guide.title5: How to Subtract Liquidity from a Pool
guide.explain1: View your current Bamboo balance: the Bamboo unstaked, the current Bamboo stake, if you have a BambooField, the seeds ready to harvest and the total Bamboo. You can refresh your balance by clicking on the double arrow
guide.explain2: Go to Wallet and click in the Buy section to exchange tokens
guide.explain3: In Settings select the Slippage and Dead Line Transition tolerance of the trades, save the changes
guide.explain4: Select the token you want to trade from and select the amount you want. You can select a percentage for ease of use
guide.explain5: Select the token you want to exchange to, the estimated amount to exchange will be reflected as well as the balance. You can select a different wallet to send the token to in Add Wallet if you wish
guide.explain6: Once the Send button is clicked, a summary of the transaction will appear for validation
guide.explain7: Once validated, the application will wait for you to confirm the transaction in your Wallet
guide.explain8: In Stake section you will see the Bamboo you can use to make Stake. By selecting the amount and time from the drop-down menus, the multiplier is displayed for your information
guide.explain9: When you click on Stake Now, a summary box is displayed for validation
guide.explain10: Select the pair you wish to provide liquidity
guide.explain11: You are informed of your position in the pool, accept by clicking on Supply
guide.explain12: When you click on Supply, you are informed of the operation and asked to validate
guide.explain13: Select the pool from which you want to withdraw liquidity
guide.explain14: Select the percentage of the pool you want to withdraw, you are informed of the amount of each token to be withdrawn. Click on approve
guide.explain15: You are informed of the pair reward, and asked for validation
guide.explain16: Select Aprobe Staking in the desired pool
guide.explain17: You are asked for confirmation in your Wallet
guide.explain18: In the active pools you can Deposit or Withdraw
guide.explain19: In Deposit select the available Seeds for the Pool, you can click on Max to include all of them, and validate the operation
guide.explain20: On clicking Withdraw, select the amount of seeds you want to withdraw, you can click on Max to include all of them, and validate the operation
guide.explain21: Display the accumulated prize in Bamboo Raindrop and in BBYP
guide.explain22: You can see the number of tickets you have bought, as well as buy tickets. The price per ticket is the one marked in the column of the respective lotteries. You can also see the date of the next lottery
guide.explain23: Here you can see your seeds and whether you have a Bamboo Field
guide.explain24: Select an active Pool and enter at least 2001 Bamboo to validate the Bamboo Field, you will open the Bamboo Field with at least one Seed. With Bamboo Field you generate an added value of 0.4% in the commission of the selected Pool in proportion to the Seeds you are growing
guide.explain25: Press Get Reward to collect the reward generated in Bamboo in the pool
